Description: Zigantic is a mobile and PC game developers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Zigantic is a mobile and pc game validation platform targeted towards game developers. Our proprietary panel consisting of high school students validate games to provide valuable insights on new features, growth mechanisms, and overall gameplay. The service utilizes influencers to learn about playing habits and patterns in hubs where mobile video games are adopted frequently. Zigantic gives game developers insights about what hooks players, identifies what causes player drop-offs and uncovers what stimulates users. We lower new product release costs, helping game developers maximize their budget for GTM activities and derive insights by connecting first-hand with players to ask deeper questions and to derive key insights for effective design feedback. We use a strong network of influencers along with a professional mobile application platform to ensure that the games receive the highest quality of reviews. Zigantic provides an entrance into desired markets for the thousands of video game development companies that require a more personal strategy.   High-schoolers, on the other hand, while providing feedback on Zigantic’s platform will learn critical thinking, analysis and reasoning while earning what is usually their first paycheck.  With over 64 million high-schoolers playing games just in the United States, and millions more across the globe in Europe and Asia, the opportunity for Zigantic is massive. Gaming has gained mainstream acceptance due to audiences ability to not only view but also interact, and it continues to grow rapidly with themes like Virtual Reality device adoption, the rise of eSports, popularization of Indie games, addition of augmented reality and game physics.    In the future, Zigantic will provide research, consulting & advisory with core expertise in game engineering, design and player behavior analysis for all VR device, Mobile and PC games developed for audiences of ages 14-24.

Description: iCents is an payment platform that enables its users to pay and earn money by joining, using, and contributing to Web 2.0 sites.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: iCents.net is a Web 2.0 payment tool, used exclusively to access content. iCents.net lets users not only pay, but also earn money by joining, using or contributing to Web 2.0 websites. It lets web developers use JavaScript and Ajax to integrate payments deep within the website's strategy. It allows people to use the payment systems they already have, like PayPal, Amazon Payments and Google Checkout, among others.  iCents.net streamlines the user experience, instead of interrupting what he or she is doing to start a payment process, and ensures that the user's experience is never disrupted. It is the first payment tool that reduces the so-called "mental transaction costs," meaning that payments using iCents require a low mental effort. This makes selling premium content easier by orders of magnitude, because the mental effort of making the payment decision itself is commonly considered the real barrier to paying for content, more so than price.  iCents.net is designed for selling premium content in mostly-free websites, under the "Freemium" business model, and provides an extra revenue model for a great number of Web 2.0 companies.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Financial Services, Other, Payments, Social Impact

Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: When you work with Weldon Law Group, PLLC, you work with a group of attorneys that understand the law. Most law firms focus on one or two topics. At Weldon Law Group, we work on a combination of immigration law, criminal defense, family law, and estate planning. One of the reasons we offer such a range of services is because we understand that our clients need more. Facing green card challenges one day, the next they may be fighting against an unjust DUI. Rather than hiring a second law firm, our clients are able to keep working with us. This approach allows us to form tighter relationships with our clients and this results in them feeling like one of the family. Ultimately, this means that working with Weldon Law Group is a much easier and more comfortable process than working with the competition. But don’t let our range of services trick you into thinking we’re anything but dedicated. Working across multiple subjects is a great way to get a better and fuller understanding of how the law functions in all its pieces. Wondering how a criminal charge is going to affect a visa? We know. Wondering if your current family law struggles are going to have an impact on your estate planning? We know the answer and we’re already reaching for the phone to offer some suggestions. Whether you need help with citizenship, green cards, visas, adjustment of immigration status, domestic violence charges, a license suspension, gun, drug, or theft crime charges, probate law, setting up a trust, or writing a will, you can rest easy knowing that Weldon Law Group’s dedicated staff are available to help. Don’t hire two law firms when all you need is one, just hire Weldon Law Group and rest easy knowing that you’re not just getting an attorney to work on this case, you’re getting an attorney that you could work with on just about anything you need legal services for.

Full Description: DoyleFab was founded in 2004 to fill a niche within the Dallas-Ft. Worth metroplex. At the time, plenty of large aerospace CNC machine shops were very capable of completing mass production orders at a competitive price, but their size became a burden when it came time to produce orders with smaller quantities. Small-scale production requires the adaptability and efficiency of a slimmer, more skilled machine shop.  Having worked as a CNC programmer and machinist for a race engine shop and as the lead of quick turn machining at an aircraft repair station, Lonny Doyle felt he had the right skillset for the job. With a single CNC mill, he started DoyleFab in one corner of the building in his backyard.  Today, DoyleFab serves customers all over the country in varying fields with the main focus still being aerospace fabrication. With a strict focus on machining efficiently, the shop has been able to satisfy customers with lower costs and quicker turn times.

Description: NewsInn is an Artificial Intelligence-Driven News Aggregator that scans the internet for news articles and delivers them to you.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: NewsInn started with a friend who tried to invest on FOREX for a little while. As it is a financial market after all, so one should be properly informed about the state of the world in order to make informed decisions. The issue was that he would spend two or three hours a day reading news articles that were all talking about the same few relevant topics. Opinions, summaries, full-length articles. He would have to read it all. That's where the idea of having a machine do this for him all started from. NewsInn is an Artificial Intelligence-Driven News Aggregator that scans the internet for news articles and delivers them based on different aspects like: Sentiment analysis, keywords, importance. It conglomerates topics into one big case, then lists all the relevant articles related to it. As we love reading the news, we observed that important sorries are covered by all major publications. But each one of them shares a slightly different point of view on the story. So the issue became the fact that we are reading the same story over and over again. So to fix that, NewsInn clusters multiple similar articles into one big single story. It is however possible that a story will appear two times on the NewsInn Feed. But this is not an error. This happens so that different points of view and different opinions on the same issue can be displayed. Another issue we always faced was to determine the opinion inserted inside the article. Knowing at a glance if the story is positive or negative, can give you a feel on the subject at hand. Besides this, there are days when you don't want to see the bad part of the world. For this, we created the "Positive" side of NewsInn. NewsInn reads the news for you and allows you to determine which full article you would like to read for further information. It also allows you to view only positive, objective or only negative articles. NewsInn is looking to become the go-to application for reading the news. It is not looking to replace major news providers, but to help our users better identify their sources of information.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

Description: Priccut is a wholesale service provider offering card-based deals across a spectrum of markets.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Priccut is an online marketing company that creates service deals that are sold in bulk. Their business model is similar to that of Costco, Sam's Club, or BJ's. These companies create deals for everyday goods that are sold in bulk or "wholesale" style. Inspired by the wholesaling of goods, Priccut applies the bulk model to services across 12 main categories according to their website: www.priccut.com. The deals created would pull from the entertainment, food, transportation, home, fitness, travel, education, electronics, and many other industries to create deals that users buy once and return several times in the future to redeem all the services purchased.  A unique aspect of the Priccut plan is the way in which customers go about redeeming these bulk deals. Consumers use a Priccut card (which is offered free of cost through their website by request to who all deals are added. Consumers then go to the  merchant location for which the deal was purchased and they receive the deal. The consumer pays no money at the merchant location unless they purchase services beyond the original deal. Priccut was founded in November  of 2011 by François N. Bessing. Then 21, he was a business student at Lehigh Carbon Community College. He dropped out in late 2012 to pursue Priccut full-time. As of December 2013, according to their Facebook page, Priccut has two live deals and they are taking steps to prepare for the next chapter in the company’s 2-year history: Series A.
